chunk_content: Please refer to the “KP_PREV” indicator to see if the services provided meet reporting criteria for that indicator as well. How to collect: This indicator provides information on the total number of individuals who have been on medication- assisted therapy (e.g., methadone, buprenorphine, or buprenorphine/naloxone to treat drug dependency) for at least 6 months within the reporting period. Consequently, data for this indicator can be generated by counting the number of individuals who are currently receiving MAT or received at least 6 months of MAT in the reporting period in accordance with the nationally approved treatment protocol (or WHO/UNAIDS standards) at the end of the reporting period. Count all individuals who have completed at least 6 months of MAT even if they drop out, die, or experience interruption in treatment, as long as they completed the minimum of 6 months of MAT within the reporting period.
